OL,3,CSummer holidays hit by inflation - as
OL,4,Chospitality prices are up 5% year on
OL,5,Cyear
OL,7,FHolidays are a key part of Wednesday's
OL,8,Frise in inflation, with hotels,
OL,9,Frestaurants, and recreation costs all
OL,10,Fincreasing faster than general
OL,11,Finflation.
OL,13,FIt was announced that UK inflation has
OL,14,Frisen for the first time since
OL,15,FDecember to 2.2%, sitting just above
OL,16,Fthe Bank of England's target.
OL,18,FAs many holidaymakers will notice,
OL,19,Fhotels and restaurant prices are up
OL,20,Faround 5% year on year.
